---
description: Server actions must authenticate and re-verify ownership before mutating
globs: src/app/**/actions.ts,src/features/**/actions/**,src/app/api/**/route.ts
---
Every server action / route handler that mutates data MUST, in order:
1. `const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser();` and `if (!user) throw` (RU message).
2. Re-verify the caller owns / is permitted on EVERY id argument before acting — never trust a
   passed-in id (see safe pattern: src/features/traveler/actions/accept-offer.ts,
   src/features/messaging/actions/offerActions.ts).
3. Use `createSupabaseServerClient()` (anon, RLS-enforced). NEVER the admin/service-role client here.
4. User-facing errors in Russian; map known RPC error substrings to friendly RU text.
RLS is the security boundary — app-layer `.eq()` filtering is NOT authorization (AGENTS.md).
